    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Predecessors to horseshoes used in the north-western parts of the Roman Empire from the mid-first century CE. The hoof was enclosed in an oval cup of thick metal, fastened by metallic clips and leather laces.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
